entries.femaleVariant: Welcome to our Zetatech Network clinic. How may I help you?
Vik. So good to see you, old ripper.
Misty Olszewski – she here?
Misty around?
What happened? Where's the store?
Here to see Viktor.
What is this? Chimes, incense, candles – where are they?
Here to see Viktor. Mind if I go through?
No one by that name is employed here, no.
You're sure to find something of the sort in town.
Do you have an appointment?
I can't now, Tyler. Drop in tomorrow.
"Drop in tomorrow"?
Was just leavin'.
Well, was on my way out, so…
Customer. I only have customers now.
Misty worked here, two years back. Gotta know somethin'.
It's a new branch. Sadly, I never met the previous owner.
Not askin' about that. Esoterica shop – that's what this was.
Well, apparently, not anymore it isn't.
Yeah, private one.
Ah, right, I see a note right here.
Please hurry in. The next patient is due to arrive soon.
Viktor, heeey…
[Give bottle] C'mon, gonna make me cry.
[Give bottle] Stuck with me, not about to go away.
[Give bottle] Well, had it wrong.
[Jack in] Well, done with major league pipe dreams, that's sure.
[Jack in] You're all I got left, Vik.
M'kay, let's do it.
Paranoid you'll confirm my diagnosis.
OK, let's get to this.
Really think this could work? Rather avoid any false hopes.
You'll be fine. Trust me.
That's the attitude.
Vektor, come on, quick. I ran into trouble, need surgery. It's my--
Ah. Are you running late?
Hey, swing by to see me anytime, yeah?
Guess you landed in some kind of shitstorm?
What can I tell you? Petrochem cocks fucked us.
Believe I told you your numbers were low.
They grabbed the better position. Pure fluke.
I got hit. Can't even tell where. But moving's hard, limited.
You're driving yourself too hard.
I'll want to hear your song after they've made me chief of security.
Mh, we'll see. Now if you don't mind, a little silence?
So none of your stale jokes, digs, put-downs?
I'd just rather not chatter.
No your style, rippah. You always seemed a lighter--
Like I said, I'd prefer no chatter.
Anyway, got ya a little somethin'.
C'mon, gonna make me cry, Vik.
What would be wrong with that?
Got it wrong, luckily.
I love that I was wrong about this one.
C'mon, you're stuck with me, not about to go away.
I'd be lyin' if I said the thought of you… gone never crossed my mind.
Wanna drink to that? I'm servin'.
To a happy return, then.
I lost, Vik, lost in life. All my plans, dreams…
You survived.
Not great. Two years and all I worked to achieve? It's in ruins.
I feel your pain, I do. But you're young. You'll find your place, a new one, in a flash.
What can I say? The world, life, they moved on, didn't wait around for me. You're all I got left.
[Jack in] All I did was in vain.
Well, your core looks fine. Good, even. Let's take a peek at your motor cortex…
Tsk, hmm.
So?
Not likin' that "hm."
So?
Can't say I like that "hm."
First time I've seen anything like this… Your cortex seems to have turned deaf to implant signals.
I... I was wrong. I'm sorry.
Said you could do something, Vik…
No goin' back – told ya.
[Jack out] You're not happy, though.
I'm limited – fuck! – and you're a corporipper.
See, Vik? Told ya – no goin' back.
[Jack out] Might be right…
[Jack out] I believe you, but we're different…
Should I start aimin' lower, too? Could be the key to happiness.
I do see it – you're plain unhappy. Pretendin' to be your former self.
You're changed, yes… but you're alive. Look at me – I had to adapt, too. Still doin' what I most love, though.
Just two years… You may not see it. Time's passed differently for me, so…
Ahem… you really think so?
It's not easy, settling. With time, though, you realize you no longer remember why you wanted it any other way.
Agh, what if I wanna remember?
I get it, Vik, I believe you. Stayed calm, level. Think I even envy you.
But that's just not me. Somethin' was taken from me. And I can't abide it.
Attitude like that can only bring pain…
Friend of yours?
[Shake hands] 'Course.
I just might.
Dunno, can't say.
'Course. 'Course I'll drop by.
Hm, I just might.
Dunno, Viktor. We'll see.
Vektor…
Close the door on your way out, OK? I need to look to Tyler's pressing problem here.
Please don't worry, Vik. Didn't come with high hopes anyway.
Not good. You have to believe there's something out there for you.
Self-delusion, that's what you advise?
Please don't worry.
So, will ya..?
Waste of words. Tried to call some old friends. Turned out you're all I got left.
I know where you're comin' from. Reach my age and you could find you have nothin' in common with those you considered near and dear.
Zetatech – how'd you wind up indentured to them?
This Zetatech thing – how'd you wind up caught in the web?
There was pressure, some threats, even… Resisting change seemed… senseless.
Misty – somehow doubt she agreed with your choice.
D'you ask Misty what she thought? Before signin' the contract?
Buyout – not the first time they tried was it?
Somethin' tells me Misty didn't go along with this… and that's why she left.
You mind if we leave that alone?
Am I wrong?
Ask Misty what she thought before you signed?
Of course I did.
Well... she said a lot of things.
She is the sensitive sort… Changes, unpleasant ones, happening all around her... She stopped feeling good here, and no wonder.
I miss her. Hope things work out for her. Hope they work out for all of us.
Whatcha actually aim to do?
We'll start with a solid scan of your body. Relax, this'll take a moment.
Vik, what happened? Signed with a corp after all?
The hell happened, Vik? So many years resistin', to let them buy you out now? Why?
They piled the pressure on, V. I mean, anonymous threats of arson included, over and over.
Wish I knew what to tell ya, kid…
Might be how it has to be.
Tried to buy you out before, right? You always said no. What changed?
I just got tired, V. The tide's strong, so strong I just can't resist it anymore.
Corp web – tough to escape once you're caught in it.
Sure hope you know what you're doin'. Corp web? Pretty hard to escape once you're caught in it.
Not to mention – you're a fuckin' honed specialist.
This chain came lookin', knockin'. Pressured me pretty hard.
Friend of yours?
No worries. Ya got a patient.
Got a patient, Vik. Don't worry about me.
No. I just want you to accept your reality.
Former clients – never liked corpos, far as I remember. They still come around?
I've lost touch with most, unfortunately. It's like we started speaking different languages.
Right, I see.
Must say I'd hoped you'd say something else.
The passage of things – fills me with fear.
Think we all could've chosen better?
Heh, funny. Was terrified I'd die for so long…
I don't see what's funny about that.
Point is, shoulda feared the passing… of all the things I knew.
Can't imagine how Johnny felt, waking up after fifty years?
You get old enough, you start coming to terms with things. Keeps you from drowning in your sentiments.
Think we could've chosen better, all of us?
No.
Hm. No hesitation.
If there'd been better options, we'd have picked them or convinced ourselves they weren't better at all.
Even you've grown cynical…
Just being honest with myself.
We all have to let go sometime. No other way.
Never liked corpos, your clients…
Why'd you choose to become a ripper in the first place?
Hey, Vik… why'd you choose to become a ripper?
Call it my youthful rebellion. All my friends at the time were gunnin' to be "somebody."
I helped 'em, fixed 'em, their bodies, minds. Though, actually just postponed the moment of their irreparable destruction.
Yeah, corpos burnout fast, fast as hell.
Well, I don't' get attached to them at least.
You've grown cynical, plain and simple.
Always did have your head square on your shoulders…
Vik – sensible as ever. And with achievable dreams. I never could settle on those.
You'll learn.
If you say so…
What're you trying to say, exactly?
Why? D'you decide you were incapable?
There came a day I realized my losses could be higher if I put my foot down.
I ran out of options, had to do what was best for the clinic.
Always got a choice, Vik, always.
If that's the case... I'd like to believe I chose well.
In a bid to survive, I gave them an indecently high price. They agreed to pay it.
What'd she say?
What the hell you wearin'?
Vik? What the hell you wearin'?
Hah. You're making a habit of this – rising from the dead.
Hang on a minute… huh, same one Jack and I knocked back. Championship bout for the middle-weight title.
Malone v Kano – remember it as if it was yesterday.
Yeah, good times… Things've changed, no denyin' it. Jackie's gone ...
So's Misty's shop.
Mh. And all her scents…
All right. Come on, hop in the chair.
So tell me – what's it like to be back among the living?
Your case? Age ain't exactly the only change.
Guess you did, right? And young you are not…
Can't function in my environment, so what's that matter?
[Jack in] Not great, kinda hard, but at least I am back.
Ain't easy, but can't call it all bad. I'm back, indefinitely, finally managed.
A hard-won victory's still a win.
And you? Feelin' like a winner these days, Vik?
Try again, please.
Check again.
V…
You'll think of somethin', Vik, I know you will. Please.
I did all I could. Don't have anywhere else to go. I'm sorry, V.
This is my friend. No affiliation to the firm. Come back later, please, it's important to me.
Hm, you got it wrong, man. You're on contract.
Tyler, please…
Vektor, nothing personal, you know. But you sew me up now, or I'll file a complaint.
Ugh... V... you can't know how sorry I am.
Whaddaya wanna do?
Ah, back off, V, they make me wear this damn thing... Something about meeting safety standards.
Doubt it, given I almost got a brain hemorrhage on seeing it.
V! How long's it been?
Depends on your point of view.
I actually thought I'd never see you again.
So damn long ago…
Ah, so many memories…
Life was simpler.
Damn, feels like another life…
Good to have memories, it grounds you.
Life was simpler somehow, wa'n't it?
Me from two years back? Gone, never gonna be her again… You know what I mean.
entries.maleVariant: Me from two years back? Gone, never gonna be him again... You know what I mean.

entries.femaleVariant: So... it's over, done.
You make it sound like you've got nothing to look forward to.
Maybe… reinstall the neuroport firmware? No, no, that'd…
Maybe switch to binary signaling…? Tsk, risk of shock… life-threatening kind.
They have this rule – no drinking anywhere in the clinic. I could get reprimanded. Wooo…
No drinking after all?
So, no drinking after all?
Relax, we'll raise a toast. Lemme fix you first.
Soo… Misty – what happened?
So Misty – tell me what happened?
She, uh, moved out not so long ago. Well, almost – drops in occasionally to collect another box of straggling sundries.
Visits are rarer and rarer, though.
Vektor, hello, I'm waitin'.
The office…. just seems colder.
Your clinic…what happened? Seems colder somehow, less cozy.
I don't suppose you're talking about the new A/C?
You know what I mean, Vik.
What can I tell ya? Corporate standards, guidelines recommendations – you match 'em. End of story.
But I daresay I managed to retain a smidge of individuality…
